The [[instrumental case]], only existing in the neuter singular, is used only with [[preposition]]s: ''{{lang|gmh|von diu}}'', ''{{lang|gmh|ze diu}}'', etc. In all the other genders and in the plural it is substituted with the dative: ''{{lang|gmh|von dëm}}'', ''{{lang|gmh|von dër}}'', ''{{lang|gmh|von dën}}''.

===Nouns===
Middle High German [[nouns]] were declined according to four [[grammatical case|cases]] ([[nominative]], [[genitive]], [[dative case|dative]], [[accusative]]), two [[grammatical number|numbers]] (singular and [[plural]]) and three [[grammatical gender|genders]] (masculine, feminine and neuter), much like Modern High German, though there are several important differences.

